data.title: Two words for you...
data.text: Mumbo wings!!  Oh my! They really are life! I'm a lover of sweet and spicy and these wings along with the rice are absolutely delicious!!!  I've tried many things at this resturant and they are ALL good choices but these wings def have this foodies heart!

data.title: Good choice
data.text: In the Courtyard Embassy row, this little gem is small but comfortable.  Service is good, the bartender is great and the food is always good.  Really can't go wrong here.

data.title: Exceptional
data.text: What a great find!!! The food and service were excellent. Everyone thoroughly enjoyed their meal; the sea scallops were excellent and the sea bass was also a favorites. Our drinks came out quickly and our meal was served hot and timely. We had a large party and our waitress happily split our checks. When we left, all our longtime friends commented how much they enjoyed our 'family meal.' Great atmosphere, drinks, food, and friends!

data.title: Nice small restaurant with excellent food
data.text: Very nice small restaurant inside the Marriott Courtyard Embassy Row. Pretty quiet on a weekday evening, being inside a hotel in the downtown commercial district with little else open around it and no pedestrian traffic. Dining room is simply decorated with interesting lighting and comfortable seating - booth seats along the wall and some tables by the window are the best.  Service was good, food very tasty and well presented. We had Romaine salad, burger, lobster crab cake (special of the day, not the lump kind but well spiced and delicious) and individual pecan pie (this is one pecan pie that's not stingy on pecans) to top off.  Menu not the most extensive but plenty to choose from.  Price reasonable, given the quality of the food was excellent value. A perfect place to go for satisfying food and quiet conversation.

data.title: Much better than your average hotel restaurant
data.text: We had breakfast at this hotel, which is attached to a Marriott Courtyard. Wide range of items, with several healthy selections. Fresh, quality food and great service. Will definitely try for another meal if we happen to stay here again.

data.title: Very nice staff and very good cuisine
data.text: We were there just for a bite and were very surprised about the quality of food and the fair prices. Staff was very attentive and genuinely nice. My friend had some shrimps and I had some scallops. Both excellent and good presentation.

data.title: Nage in DC ... who knew?
data.text: We stayed at the Courtyard Embassy Row and noticed the same restaurant we visit in Rehoboth Beach, DE.  This is nice little bistro & wine bar that offers a variety of fresh food options.

data.title: Great food, AWESOME STAFF
data.text: We ate breakfast here during our stay at the Courtyard by Marriott.  Brandy was awesome. Her personality and and being so upbeat was a great way to start our busy days.  The food was great and very filling.  Thanks to the staff for starting our day off on a great beat!

data.title: Good Food, Poorly Managed
data.text: We visited for brunch to celebrate a birthday.  Reservations went well and we were seated promptly, but things went downhill quickly.  Our server was friendly, but she seemed to be the only one taking care orders from every table (though she wasn't, she was clearly being overworked).  Two tables around us were yelling so loud I could barely hear the person sitting next to me.  A number of tables around made eye contact with each other during nearly continuous outbursts and Mgt just ignored it.  The food came and was fairly good...particularly the Chesapeake eggs Benedict, but the noise was so overwhelming that we simply couldn't enjoy the meal.  We finished as quickly as possible to escape from the literal headaches at the handful of inconsiderate guests that were never asked to respect the rest of us, but the check was very slow.  Our poor waitress was as fast as possible.  The seven of us were finally delivered a check with automatic 20% gratuity and on our way out let management know of the unpleasant experience and told we should have alerted them. The guests shouldn't have to complain for Mgt to survey the dining room floor and be proactive to assure the rest of us are not run out by a few inconsiderate guests. The kitchen and waitress did the best they could, but management needs to manage their dining room much better.  We will not be back.

data.title: Restaurant worst service ever
data.text: Hotel was fine, but we decided due to time constraints to just eat breakfast at the hotel's restaurant.  What a mistake.  Service was ridiculously slow, food items came out separately, as much as 5 minutes from the first to the last, and couldn't even get sweetener on the table after asking twice.  To top it all off, the prices were high.

data.title: The food was excellent .
data.text: We had breakfast , lunch and dinner here.  It is a small Restaurant attached to the Marriott Hotel. All three meals were outstanding.  The service was friendly, the atmosphere was quaint .

data.title: Good hotel restaurant
data.text: Food is very good, but menu is not extensive.  Service is very good.  Five blocks from the White House.  Small dining area.  Clean.  Good full bar.  Booths and tables.  Not white tablecloth.  Really a very decent small hotel restaurant.

data.title: Excellent Food
data.text: I ordered an Angus Burger 10 minutes before closing and they graciously accomodated me. I ordered ahead and was called when the food was ready. I didn't too much care for the bartender ignoring me  for 3 minutes to continue a conversation she was having with a bar customer as my food sat on the bar getting cold. The burger was delicious and so were the fries. I would recommend this meal.

data.title: Try brunch here!
data.text:
I went to brunch at Nage because my intended destination did not have pancakes.
I have been back 8 times since that 'unintended' visit. 
The food is a mix of Southern, Soul and French provincial (Trust me it works).
The Chef, Dwayne is gifted and inventive.

data.title: 5 Star Quality
data.text: I had numerous items on the menu for breakfast, lunch, and dinner and would recommend them all. It is a quaint restaurant with style. The food is presented in a manner that makes you feel as if you were dining at a 5 star restaurant without the price. The chef makes a variety of options each week but the all natural burger is always a good option.

data.title: Dc has more to offer
data.text: Was looking for a restaurant near my hotel and was recommended Nage.  This little spot was ok , nothing special. A one and done

data.title: Give it a try
data.text: We came here simply because we found a parking place practically next-door when going to the National Geographic Museum. I knew nothing about it but was attracted by the word bistro on the awning. I wasn't disappointed although I'm not going give it a rave review. The staff is, shall we say, not polished but they are sincere. My table was wiped with a pretty dirty cloth and I asked for it to be re-wiped with a dry paper towel. Which was done with dispatch. I ordered the mushroom baklava (which is really a blini) but asked them to hold the berry sauce as I just don't like so much sweet with my savory. Also ordered the kale salad which was excellent. They had blanched it enough so I didn't have to spend so much time chewing. The veggie burger with gazpacho soup my husband ordered were all excellent. We will not go out of our way to come here again but won't avoid it either.

data.title: Reasonable food
data.text: We loved the happy hour at this hotel restaurant especially the oysters which were delicious. The bar tender was attentive to our request with efficient service. I also tried dinner here and loved the garden salad but was disappointed with the French onion soup (taste was a bit weird).

data.title: Beautiful Food!
data.text: Very friendly staff and delicious food. Breakfast was amazing and Lamb Shanks were the best I've ever eaten.

data.title: Disappointed
data.text: Made reservations but place was pretty much empty at 8pm on friday. weird but ok. all staff looked like they just got back from big party - hangover and not really clean/neat appearance. food was alright nothing great. asked for tea bags as staying at hotel this restaurant located at ans was charged $1 for it with manager basically throwing it at me without any choice for flavor. before we could leave they were cleaning our table. so unprofessional so disappointed..
